Efforts to oust deputy president William Ruto as Jubilee deputy party leader has divided the ruling party&rsquo;s hierarchy right down the middle. It is now emerging that some members of the powerful national management committee have been piling pressure on President Uhuru Kenyatta, who is the party leader, to convene the party&rsquo;s national executive committee on Tuesday this week to proceed with the ouster, while another faction has adopted a more wait-and-see approach.